  daily turnover of the supervised entity concerned per day of
  infringement, and they may be imposed for a maximum period of six
  months from the date stipulated in the relevant decision or
  regulation. By contrast, administrative pecuniary penalties imposed
  by the ECB may amount to up to twice the amount of the profits
  gained or losses avoided because of the breach, or up to 10% of the
  supervised entity's total annual turnover in the preceding business
  year. (ECB Supervisory Manual, pages 105, 107)
